One of my favorite places to go to Chinatown. It’s cheap but the food is delicious. You don’t even have to worry about going alone bc usually only 1/2 people sit at each table. Their rice noodles are amazing and i would also recommend their Sweet Bread and alovera drink😋😋. The serving since it big for what you pay and i promise you most people are not able to finish the entire thing!! The place is clean and the mood is very nice.

The buns are very delicious. I particularly like their XiaoLongBao and pork bun. The pork bun is an open bun design, not the traditional way. But the XiaoLongBao has a juicy thick skin just like the northern style buns.
First time having pork bao as an American, delicious. Noodles were served like a king. Enjoyed every bite, great cold weather food.

The same modality doesn't yield the same taste. For those who seek authentic Yunnan noodles, the authenticity is off the discussion. However, disregarding the authenticity, the noodles and the buns themselves taste alright. I'll say that this is one of those restaurants where you'll find the taste to be OK but just not quite enough.
Great service and a great experience

Great beef noodle soup at cheap prices. Try the  hot and spicy and any of the proteins, they are all delicious. If you like intestines I recommend that one!  The noodles are not your traditional ones, the thick rice noodles, kind of like a less dense springy-er udon noodle. They are really great for noodles and hard to find places that serve these. The broth is beefy and strong. The extras are all great and the meats are all flavorful and fresh. Overall a delicious filling meal for $10.  You should definitely stop by and try a bowl, I promise you it'll be great!
Delicious noodles, friendly staff, and clean restaurant. I'll definitely be back for more.
Great hot pots.

This place offers a list of soup stocks that you add a variety of protein. They don't have any vegetarian option listed but I got the curry version without protein. The Curry flavors were typical East Asian but it lacked heat. Fortunately they offer things to add to that punch up the flavor. I also ordered a wood ear mushroom salad that had wonderful depth of flavor. I think meat eaters will enjoy this a lot more than I did.
I like food but it only serves noodle soup with different meats

(Translated by Google) Noodle shop selling Chinese rice noodles. It is a noodle restaurant with soup, noodles, and toppings in pottery. Normally, the staff will take care of it, but you can change the order by yourself. Combine meat, broth sauce, and noodles. The broth sauce is tomato, spicy, and so on. The original taste is as clear as the soup. No other side menus are recommended. The price and atmosphere are also good. It is a very suitable menu for drinking and dissolving.  (Original) 중국의 쌀국수를 파는 면집. 도기에 국물과 면, 토핑들이 다 따로나오는 국수식당이다. 보통은 직원들이 알아서 넣어주지만 혼자서 순서를 바꿔서 넣어먹을 수 있다. 고기와 국물 소스, 그리고 면을 조합해서 시킨다. 국물 소스는 토마토, 매운 맛, 등등이 있는데 오리지널 맛은 곰국처럼 맑은 국물이다. 다른 사이드 메뉴는 추천하지 않는다. 가격과 분위기도 무난한 곳이다. 술먹고 해장하기에 아주 적합한 메뉴이다.

Noodle was okay but broth didn’t have too much flavor. The noodle I got was crossing the bridge noodles which came with a lot of sides and I would say part of the fun is making it by choosing how to put in all your sides but the employees brought over the piping hot bowl of noodle and then just helped toss all the sides into it to quickly clear all the plates

Visited on a Wednesday night around 9pm and we ordered the brisket noodle and beef shank noodles. They were served super fast, no wait time which was great and the waitresses were patient and helpful in explaining the menu. I loved the beef brisket it was super tender and way better than yummy yummy noodles down the street, definitely try the brisket. As for the beef shank it was good but but I prefer the beef shank at yummy yummy noodles. I got the sour and spicy broth which is superb! Slight spice not really sour and not over bearing, my friend got the original broth, too bland she said, and my bf got the hot and spicy broth which was super hott but he likes the spicyness. I would have given 5 stars but they only offer one type of noodle, I would have liked options, but the noodle they served was good just would have liked to try other kinds. Roughly $10 for a bowl, a bit above average compared to other noodle places in Chinatown but I highly recommend! I would come back. Great service and noodles!

I have good experiences here but also bad experiences and it feels like it can vary a lot based on who's there that day and how busy things are. Generally, it's not authentic, but hey their mi xian noodles tastes pretty good. Portions are very small though, but other than that I have no complaints.  Will recommend if you want to try something new.

Solid potent broth with a cool presentation! They throw in all the ingredients in boiling soup inside the stone bowl.  If you're looking for an extra kick, they have Szechuan peppercorn oil you can add. The rice noodles are about too over cooked for my preference, but that may be how it's supposed to be.  I got hot and sour soup with pork chops which seemed to work well together!  The service wasn't as terrible as others suggest, but it also wasn't the best ... Just average.  Overall I'll return and try more combinations!

Highly recommend! I was there with my wife in weekend. The service was great and thoughtful. I’m a Muslim and can’t eat pork, but all noodle dishes contained pork soup as base. So kitchen offered special option with no pork added, even in soup. The flavor was way too beyond what I thought, and that was soooo good.  Cold day having hot soup dish was completely joyful.  Thank you for being thoughtful and we definitely will come back.

I can't speak to authenticity, as I'm not from Yunnan, but this is pretty damn tasty stuff, especially for the winter. They don't skimp on the flavours (or hot oil) to keep those noodles at a mouth-burning temperature. I don't think this place necessarily deserves a Bib Gourmand (the Michelin guide pretty much is useless outside traditional western cuisine), but it hits the spot for when you want a decent bowl of Chinese noodles.
